1
00:00:06,065 --> 00:00:09,665
I'll leave you, Grandma,
and never come back.

2
00:00:09,745 --> 00:00:12,785
The two of us
have both been running from love.

3
00:00:12,865 --> 00:00:16,505
<i>If I can start over, then so can you.</i>

4
00:00:16,585 --> 00:00:18,745
<i>Can I ask you something honestly?</i>

5
00:00:18,825 --> 00:00:20,465
Why did you help me?

6
00:00:21,065 --> 00:00:25,825
Would you mind if I wanted to date you?

7
00:00:25,905 --> 00:00:27,465
Who is this woman to you?

8
00:00:27,545 --> 00:00:29,465
I don't think we should be together.

9
00:00:49,585 --> 00:00:50,665
Piang.

10
00:00:56,985 --> 00:00:57,825
It's me.

11
00:00:58,425 --> 00:00:59,585
Are you asleep?

12
00:01:13,345 --> 00:01:14,505
Hello?

13
00:01:14,585 --> 00:01:15,625
Where are you?

14
00:01:16,705 --> 00:01:18,385
<i>Hello, I'm from the rescue team.</i>

15
00:01:19,025 --> 00:01:21,225
<i>Do you know the owner of this phone?</i>

16
00:01:21,305 --> 00:01:22,265
What?

17
00:01:25,145 --> 00:01:27,105
<i>She was hit by a car.</i>

18
00:01:27,185 --> 00:01:28,465
Huh?

19
00:01:28,545 --> 00:01:29,705
What?

20
00:01:30,505 --> 00:01:32,265
Where is she?

21
00:01:32,345 --> 00:01:33,945
<i>In front of Saint Che Hotel.</i>

22
00:01:34,025 --> 00:01:36,705
<i>We're rushing her to the hospital now.</i>

23
00:01:36,785 --> 00:01:39,385
CHAI

24
00:01:44,705 --> 00:01:46,625
Why are you calling so late?

25
00:01:46,705 --> 00:01:48,985
<i>Madam, Ms. Piang…</i>

26
00:02:08,505 --> 00:02:09,625
Grandma.

27
00:02:11,425 --> 00:02:13,985
Grandma. Grandma.

28
00:02:16,985 --> 00:02:17,985
Piang.

29
00:02:19,225 --> 00:02:20,305
Piang.

30
00:02:21,225 --> 00:02:23,025
What happened to Piang?

31
00:02:24,305 --> 00:02:25,745
Grandma.

32
00:02:26,945 --> 00:02:28,065
Grandma.

33
00:02:29,185 --> 00:02:30,625
Grandma, Grandma.

34
00:02:31,465 --> 00:02:32,865
Piang.

35
00:04:33,745 --> 00:04:35,625
Song, what happened?

36
00:04:35,705 --> 00:04:37,625
How did Piang get hit by a car?

37
00:04:39,145 --> 00:04:41,225
-I'm not sure either.
-But you were with her.

38
00:04:41,905 --> 00:04:43,345
Then you must know.

39
00:04:45,345 --> 00:04:46,945
Please calm down, Grandma.

40
00:04:48,305 --> 00:04:51,145
Song, go sit down and rest.

41
00:04:51,225 --> 00:04:52,065
Trust me.

42
00:04:53,425 --> 00:04:54,665
Yes, Boss.

43
00:05:06,585 --> 00:05:07,785
Doctor.

44
00:05:09,585 --> 00:05:11,105
How's Piang?

45
00:05:12,345 --> 00:05:13,985
She hasn't regained consciousness yet.

46
00:05:14,065 --> 00:05:15,225
But she's out of danger.

47
00:05:16,025 --> 00:05:18,385
She suffered a head injury.

48
00:05:18,465 --> 00:05:21,985
But her CT scan shows no brain bleeding.

49
00:05:22,585 --> 00:05:25,225
She only has a few minor scrapes.

50
00:05:25,305 --> 00:05:27,225
She also has a fractured wrist.

51
00:05:27,305 --> 00:05:30,345
Once she regains consciousness,
she'll be able to go home.

52
00:05:30,945 --> 00:05:35,705
But for the next week or two,
please keep a close eye on her.

53
00:05:35,785 --> 00:05:39,225
If she develops a headache
or starts vomiting,

54
00:05:39,305 --> 00:05:40,625
bring her back right away.

55
00:05:40,705 --> 00:05:42,585
Sometimes brain bleeding

56
00:05:42,665 --> 00:05:45,265
doesn't show up until some time
after the accident.

57
00:05:45,345 --> 00:05:47,025
It can be delayed.

58
00:05:48,785 --> 00:05:50,865
But it doesn't happen very often.

59
00:05:51,905 --> 00:05:54,025
Try not to worry too much, Song.

60
00:05:55,865 --> 00:05:57,265
Doctor, you know me?

61
00:05:59,185 --> 00:06:00,665
Of course I do.

62
00:06:00,745 --> 00:06:02,865
Piang has told me about you.

63
00:06:04,585 --> 00:06:05,665
I see.

64
00:06:05,745 --> 00:06:07,625
Then you two must be really close.

65
00:06:08,625 --> 00:06:09,745
Not really.

66
00:06:09,825 --> 00:06:11,025
It's more like I was forced to.

67
00:06:12,305 --> 00:06:14,625
Do you want to know
what Piang said about you?

68
00:06:16,025 --> 00:06:17,105
No, thanks.

69
00:06:18,225 --> 00:06:20,065
But I think you should know.

70
00:06:27,625 --> 00:06:29,545
Is the patient okay?

71
00:06:29,625 --> 00:06:31,225
Yes, they're safe.

72
00:06:33,385 --> 00:06:34,865
I'll take you home.

73
00:06:39,425 --> 00:06:40,945
Namking.

74
00:06:42,185 --> 00:06:45,865
There's something I need to tell you.

75
00:06:57,865 --> 00:06:59,665
What is it, Piang?

76
00:07:05,305 --> 00:07:07,225
I already like someone else.

77
00:07:08,425 --> 00:07:12,985
Even if we keep dating,
I'll never fall for you.

78
00:07:19,945 --> 00:07:20,985
Okay.

79
00:07:24,025 --> 00:07:25,145
Same here.

80
00:07:26,625 --> 00:07:27,465
What?

81
00:07:28,145 --> 00:07:30,505
Namking, you like someone too?

82
00:07:31,025 --> 00:07:32,905
No, it's just…

83
00:07:33,425 --> 00:07:35,105
I don't plan on liking anyone.

84
00:07:36,505 --> 00:07:41,025
As you can see,
my work keeps me very busy.

85
00:07:42,625 --> 00:07:47,545
If I had a partner,
I don't think I'd take good care of them.

86
00:07:49,865 --> 00:07:51,345
But I'm curious.

87
00:07:51,425 --> 00:07:55,545
If you already like someone,
why did you go on a date with me?

88
00:07:56,985 --> 00:07:59,665
Or… were you just doing
what Grandma asked?

89
00:08:00,465 --> 00:08:01,745
That's part of it.

90
00:08:02,705 --> 00:08:06,345
But the person I like,
doesn't feel the same.

91
00:08:06,425 --> 00:08:09,945
So I thought I'd try opening
my heart to someone else.

92
00:08:10,025 --> 00:08:11,425
Did it work?

93
00:08:12,025 --> 00:08:13,905
No, it didn't.

94
00:08:14,505 --> 00:08:17,265
That's why I wanted to be honest with you.

95
00:08:19,345 --> 00:08:23,545
Do you remember the woman we passed
after leaving the party?

96
00:08:40,345 --> 00:08:42,945
That was her. Her name is Song.

97
00:08:44,345 --> 00:08:45,905
And I'm deeply in love with her.

98
00:08:46,785 --> 00:08:49,065
She's my first love.

99
00:08:51,665 --> 00:08:52,825
Then…

100
00:08:54,105 --> 00:08:56,585
I think you should give it one more try.

101
00:08:57,945 --> 00:09:00,505
<i>Piang said you don't like her,</i>

102
00:09:01,105 --> 00:09:03,345
but what I see says otherwise.

103
00:09:03,865 --> 00:09:05,145
You're worried about her,

104
00:09:05,225 --> 00:09:07,545
and you're uncomfortable
seeing me with her.

105
00:09:08,345 --> 00:09:10,305
If that's not love, then what is?

106
00:09:12,585 --> 00:09:14,505
Don't run from your own heart.

107
00:09:15,905 --> 00:09:19,865
And if you're worried about Grandma,
I'll find a way to help you.

108
00:09:19,945 --> 00:09:21,025
There's no need.

109
00:09:22,905 --> 00:09:25,465
I heard every word.

110
00:09:33,345 --> 00:09:35,865
I'd like a word
with this young lady alone.

111
00:09:45,705 --> 00:09:47,025
Do you understand now

112
00:09:47,785 --> 00:09:52,425
why I've been trying to keep you away
from my granddaughter?

113
00:09:53,145 --> 00:09:57,465
You're not only unworthy of her,
you diminish her worth.

114
00:09:57,545 --> 00:10:00,065
You can't even protect her.

115
00:10:01,705 --> 00:10:03,425
I just don't understand

116
00:10:03,945 --> 00:10:07,065
how Piang could ever fall
for someone like you.

117
00:10:17,745 --> 00:10:20,265
Then please give me just two weeks.

118
00:10:21,785 --> 00:10:25,145
Just two weeks to stay by Piang's side

119
00:10:25,225 --> 00:10:28,105
and take care of her
until she's fully recovered.

120
00:10:29,305 --> 00:10:30,745
After that,

121
00:10:31,345 --> 00:10:33,305
I'll never let her see me again.

122
00:10:33,385 --> 00:10:35,065
You've said that before.

123
00:10:35,825 --> 00:10:37,105
But you never kept your word.

124
00:10:37,185 --> 00:10:39,265
This time, I promise.

125
00:11:08,225 --> 00:11:11,625
That woman promised me
she'd stop seeing Piang.

126
00:11:12,865 --> 00:11:17,585
But she asked for two weeks
to care for Piang until she's recovered.

127
00:11:20,345 --> 00:11:21,385
Okay.

128
00:11:25,345 --> 00:11:27,425
Don't you have anything to say?

129
00:11:29,145 --> 00:11:30,145
No.

130
00:11:30,665 --> 00:11:32,425
I'll leave it to your judgment.

131
00:11:36,425 --> 00:11:38,665
If that's all, I'll get going.

132
00:11:42,505 --> 00:11:43,345
Mudmee.

133
00:11:46,545 --> 00:11:47,745
Yes?

134
00:11:51,385 --> 00:11:53,185
-I slapped you…
-I know, Grandma.

135
00:11:55,985 --> 00:11:58,545
And now that woman has broken up with me.

136
00:12:00,145 --> 00:12:02,225
You won't have to worry anymore.

137
00:12:02,825 --> 00:12:05,025
I won't disappoint you again.

138
00:12:45,505 --> 00:12:46,425
Piang.

139
00:12:48,585 --> 00:12:49,785
How are you feeling?

140
00:12:51,425 --> 00:12:52,465
Song.

141
00:12:57,585 --> 00:12:58,745
Don't lift it.

142
00:13:00,185 --> 00:13:01,225
Your wrist is fractured.

143
00:13:02,025 --> 00:13:03,745
If you need anything, tell me.

144
00:13:08,665 --> 00:13:09,985
My head hurts.

145
00:13:10,585 --> 00:13:11,625
Is it bad?

146
00:13:12,345 --> 00:13:13,665
Do you feel like throwing up?

147
00:13:17,105 --> 00:13:19,585
The doctor said it'd be
like this for a while.

148
00:13:19,665 --> 00:13:22,705
As long as it doesn't get worse,
there's nothing to worry about.

149
00:13:25,945 --> 00:13:27,345
Hang in there.

150
00:13:36,225 --> 00:13:38,945
Why did you go out by yourself?

151
00:13:39,025 --> 00:13:41,665
Didn't I tell you to come get me
if you needed anything?

152
00:13:42,425 --> 00:13:45,065
It was already late.

153
00:13:45,585 --> 00:13:46,825
I didn't want to bother you.

154
00:13:47,585 --> 00:13:50,065
You always make me worry.

155
00:13:56,105 --> 00:13:58,785
So you finally admit you worry about me?

156
00:14:05,305 --> 00:14:06,305
Yeah.

157
00:14:07,065 --> 00:14:08,185
I do worry about you.

158
00:14:17,345 --> 00:14:19,065
I'm so happy.

159
00:14:20,025 --> 00:14:22,505
I never thought I'd hear you say that.

160
00:14:26,945 --> 00:14:28,585
Could you say it more often?

161
00:14:30,065 --> 00:14:31,305
No.

162
00:14:34,065 --> 00:14:36,425
No one says that all the time.

163
00:14:37,025 --> 00:14:39,465
It means there's always
something to worry about.

164
00:14:40,025 --> 00:14:41,665
Then use a different word instead.

165
00:14:43,665 --> 00:14:46,905
What word should it be?

166
00:14:47,665 --> 00:14:50,385
How about using your own name?

167
00:14:52,505 --> 00:14:55,825
I like it when you call yourself "Song"
instead of "I."

168
00:14:56,785 --> 00:14:58,585
It just feels warmer.

169
00:15:00,425 --> 00:15:01,705
When did you hear that?

170
00:15:01,785 --> 00:15:03,625
You really want me to say it?

171
00:15:05,385 --> 00:15:06,545
Well…

172
00:15:06,625 --> 00:15:09,865
When we slept together.

173
00:15:09,945 --> 00:15:11,105
You don't have to say it.

174
00:15:11,625 --> 00:15:12,905
I know.

175
00:15:31,185 --> 00:15:32,265
Hello.

176
00:15:38,665 --> 00:15:40,425
I'd like to speak with my granddaughter.

177
00:15:40,505 --> 00:15:41,705
Of course.

178
00:15:47,145 --> 00:15:49,585
I'll be back, Grandma.

179
00:15:49,665 --> 00:15:50,585
Mm.

180
00:15:56,825 --> 00:15:58,345
Grandma, why are you here?

181
00:15:59,545 --> 00:16:01,385
Or are you here to make me
feel even worse?

182
00:16:01,465 --> 00:16:03,025
I don't feel anything.

183
00:16:05,465 --> 00:16:09,585
I'm here to make you a deal
about that woman.

184
00:16:12,425 --> 00:16:17,025
The more I tried to stop you,
the worse things got.

185
00:16:18,065 --> 00:16:20,225
I'll let you date her.

186
00:16:21,345 --> 00:16:22,265
What?

187
00:16:22,785 --> 00:16:23,865
But there's one condition.

188
00:16:24,465 --> 00:16:28,345
You have two weeks
to make her fall for you.

189
00:16:28,945 --> 00:16:34,505
If you can't,
then accept the truth and let her go.

190
00:16:35,225 --> 00:16:36,945
Why two weeks?

191
00:16:37,465 --> 00:16:43,065
Because when you're chasing someone,
you should set a time limit,

192
00:16:43,145 --> 00:16:45,105
not chase them forever.

193
00:16:46,025 --> 00:16:48,905
If she's really going to love you back,

194
00:16:48,985 --> 00:16:54,865
then two weeks should be
more than enough time to decide.

195
00:16:56,385 --> 00:16:57,225
Do we have a deal?

196
00:17:02,265 --> 00:17:03,425
Deal.

197
00:17:05,345 --> 00:17:06,345
Good.

198
00:17:17,424 --> 00:17:18,505
Careful.

199
00:17:38,465 --> 00:17:40,985
If you throw up a lot tonight
or get a bad headache,

200
00:17:41,065 --> 00:17:42,945
call me right away.

201
00:17:44,505 --> 00:17:45,425
Okay.

202
00:17:46,225 --> 00:17:49,705
So… you're really not staying
with me tonight?

203
00:17:53,625 --> 00:17:56,185
I'm afraid I'll bump your wrist
and hurt you.

204
00:18:21,465 --> 00:18:22,625
<i>Just two weeks.</i>

205
00:18:22,705 --> 00:18:24,025
<i>Let me stay with Piang</i>

206
00:18:24,945 --> 00:18:27,745
and take care of her
until she's fully recovered.

207
00:18:28,785 --> 00:18:30,345
After that,

208
00:18:31,105 --> 00:18:33,145
I'll never let her see me again.

209
00:18:42,945 --> 00:18:46,225
<i>You have two weeks</i>
<i>to make her fall for you.</i>

210
00:18:47,505 --> 00:18:53,665
If you can't,
then accept the truth and let her go.

211
00:19:14,665 --> 00:19:16,225
-Oh.
-Oh.

212
00:19:16,305 --> 00:19:17,585
Where are you going?

213
00:19:18,105 --> 00:19:19,545
What about you?

214
00:19:20,065 --> 00:19:21,745
I was on my way to see you.

215
00:19:24,265 --> 00:19:25,465
Song.

216
00:19:25,985 --> 00:19:27,905
I want to get out of town.

217
00:19:28,505 --> 00:19:31,425
I don't want to stay
cooped up in this room.

218
00:19:32,465 --> 00:19:33,625
Please.

219
00:19:34,225 --> 00:19:38,385
Fresh air and beautiful scenery
might help me recover faster.

220
00:19:41,705 --> 00:19:42,865
What a coincidence.

221
00:19:43,385 --> 00:19:45,225
I was about to ask you too.

222
00:19:48,385 --> 00:19:50,425
-You mean…
-Let's go together.

223
00:20:25,625 --> 00:20:27,345
Why did you choose this place?

224
00:20:28,305 --> 00:20:31,225
Do you remember when I told you

225
00:20:31,305 --> 00:20:33,425
my parents brought me
to see the sea of mist?

226
00:20:38,825 --> 00:20:40,345
This is the place.

227
00:20:42,185 --> 00:20:44,945
Where's the mist? I don't see any.

228
00:20:45,025 --> 00:20:47,225
All I see is smoke from forest fires.

229
00:20:47,305 --> 00:20:48,465
And the PM pollution.

230
00:20:49,065 --> 00:20:50,065
Song.

231
00:20:50,145 --> 00:20:51,705
What? I was just asking.

232
00:20:51,785 --> 00:20:53,705
That was during winter.

233
00:20:53,785 --> 00:20:55,625
It's summer now.

234
00:20:55,705 --> 00:20:57,185
How could there be any mist?

235
00:21:04,905 --> 00:21:09,305
Even without it, it's still beautiful.

236
00:21:15,105 --> 00:21:17,945
Because it's full of memories.

237
00:21:27,905 --> 00:21:29,225
You forgot again.

238
00:21:41,985 --> 00:21:43,705
I'm sorry.

239
00:21:44,825 --> 00:21:46,865
I ruined the mood.

240
00:21:48,225 --> 00:21:50,025
I'm the one who should be sorry.

241
00:21:50,625 --> 00:21:54,625
I wanted to comfort you,
but I didn't know how.

242
00:21:56,785 --> 00:21:59,545
I've lost someone in my family too.

243
00:22:00,145 --> 00:22:04,665
Even now, whenever I think of them,
I still can't fully move on.

244
00:22:08,705 --> 00:22:11,425
Then I guess we feel the same.

245
00:22:15,105 --> 00:22:18,785
If you want to comfort me,
you don't have to do much.

246
00:22:19,545 --> 00:22:22,865
Just wipe away my tears,
and I'll feel better.

247
00:22:23,705 --> 00:22:26,825
Then cry again, so I can wipe your tears.

248
00:22:27,665 --> 00:22:28,985
Song.

249
00:23:23,185 --> 00:23:24,665
Song.

250
00:23:34,945 --> 00:23:36,305
Song.

251
00:23:37,785 --> 00:23:39,265
Song.

252
00:23:45,425 --> 00:23:46,665
You're awake?

253
00:23:46,745 --> 00:23:48,065
I am.

254
00:23:48,145 --> 00:23:50,385
When did I fall asleep?

255
00:23:50,465 --> 00:23:51,985
Right after you took your medicine.

256
00:23:53,825 --> 00:23:55,265
These meds…

257
00:23:55,345 --> 00:23:57,545
I'm throwing them all away.
I'm not taking them anymore.

258
00:23:57,625 --> 00:23:59,105
Why are you being so stubborn?

259
00:23:59,185 --> 00:24:00,545
I'm not being stubborn.

260
00:24:01,385 --> 00:24:04,745
I just don't want to miss
a single moment with you.

261
00:24:06,105 --> 00:24:09,465
If we sleep, we sleep together.

262
00:24:10,065 --> 00:24:12,505
And if we shower,

263
00:24:13,585 --> 00:24:15,025
we shower together.

264
00:24:32,745 --> 00:24:36,945
After saying that,
why are you still just standing there?

265
00:25:37,825 --> 00:25:40,545
So we don't have to
sleep back-to-back anymore?

266
00:26:21,585 --> 00:26:22,465
Piang.

267
00:26:28,065 --> 00:26:29,385
Don't be naughty.

268
00:26:30,385 --> 00:26:31,825
You're still injured.

269
00:26:32,425 --> 00:26:34,225
Does that mean

270
00:26:35,345 --> 00:26:37,705
once my hand is healed,

271
00:26:38,585 --> 00:26:40,905
you won't stop me anymore?

272
00:27:21,625 --> 00:27:23,745
Hold on. I need to take this call.

273
00:27:29,865 --> 00:27:30,945
<i>Where are you?</i>

274
00:27:31,025 --> 00:27:32,985
I'm out of town with Piang.

275
00:27:33,065 --> 00:27:35,225
<i>What? Seriously?</i>

276
00:27:35,305 --> 00:27:38,465
You just got out of the hospital
and went on a romantic trip?

277
00:27:38,545 --> 00:27:39,545
<i>It's not like that.</i>

278
00:27:40,145 --> 00:27:44,145
Piang just wanted a change of scenery,
so she asked me to bring her here.

279
00:27:44,225 --> 00:27:45,985
<i>And you said yes.</i>

280
00:27:46,065 --> 00:27:50,905
Song, did you tell her about it
and work things out?

281
00:27:52,865 --> 00:27:53,945
No.

282
00:27:54,545 --> 00:27:56,465
<i>What's wrong with you?</i>

283
00:27:56,545 --> 00:27:57,945
<i>What are you waiting for?</i>

284
00:27:58,465 --> 00:28:00,025
I'm not waiting.

285
00:28:00,545 --> 00:28:03,465
I just don't have much time left with her.

286
00:28:03,545 --> 00:28:05,745
I don't want any more drama.

287
00:28:06,985 --> 00:28:10,385
I'd rather spend
the time I have left well.

288
00:28:10,465 --> 00:28:11,425
What?

289
00:28:12,265 --> 00:28:13,425
<i>I've got to go.</i>

290
00:28:30,745 --> 00:28:34,505
Here's your hot spaghetti.

291
00:28:35,065 --> 00:28:37,665
-Here.
-Is this Chef Ploy?

292
00:28:37,745 --> 00:28:39,465
-Does it look good?
-It looks amazing.

293
00:28:39,545 --> 00:28:43,585
Homemade bacon, mushrooms,
sauce, everything's homemade.

294
00:28:43,665 --> 00:28:45,705
You're the ultimate food researcher.

295
00:28:45,785 --> 00:28:47,825
So what did Song say?

296
00:28:49,225 --> 00:28:50,705
She said something strange.

297
00:28:50,785 --> 00:28:52,865
Something about not having much time left.

298
00:28:52,945 --> 00:28:55,825
Like she's counting down
the time she has with Piang.

299
00:28:57,305 --> 00:28:59,145
-Really?
-Yeah.

300
00:29:08,985 --> 00:29:11,065
Why don't you eat first?

301
00:29:11,145 --> 00:29:14,945
You can't worry so much
about your friend that you forget to eat.

302
00:29:15,025 --> 00:29:16,265
That's not good.

303
00:29:16,945 --> 00:29:18,065
Okay.

304
00:29:18,145 --> 00:29:20,225
Then feed me.

305
00:29:20,305 --> 00:29:25,105
Just now, I used up all my energy
worrying about my friend.

306
00:29:25,185 --> 00:29:27,065
-Really?
-Mm.

307
00:29:27,865 --> 00:29:29,025
Get up.

308
00:29:29,105 --> 00:29:30,825
I'll feed you. Come on.

309
00:29:32,065 --> 00:29:34,385
I'll give you a huge bite.

310
00:29:34,985 --> 00:29:36,985
-Go on, feed me.
-It smells so good.

311
00:29:37,065 --> 00:29:38,145
Does it?

312
00:29:41,145 --> 00:29:42,505
Looks like I'll eat it tomorrow.

313
00:29:44,105 --> 00:29:45,065
Here.

314
00:29:49,785 --> 00:29:51,025
So that's how you want to play?

315
00:30:00,185 --> 00:30:01,825
-How is it?
-Delicious.

316
00:30:02,345 --> 00:30:03,905
-Really?
-Mm.

317
00:30:04,425 --> 00:30:05,865
Of course it is. I made it.

318
00:30:06,585 --> 00:30:07,905
My turn.

319
00:30:17,945 --> 00:30:19,465
PLE PIJIKAA

320
00:30:19,545 --> 00:30:23,625
SOMSAK2511

321
00:30:39,065 --> 00:30:40,345
Is something wrong?

322
00:30:41,025 --> 00:30:42,025
No.

323
00:30:47,585 --> 00:30:49,625
Okay, let's keep eating.

324
00:30:49,705 --> 00:30:51,945
Here, some fresh salad.

325
00:30:57,865 --> 00:31:00,185
-How is it? Is it good?
-It's delicious.

326
00:31:00,265 --> 00:31:02,265
-I picked it myself.
-I like this one better.

327
00:31:14,985 --> 00:31:16,185
You spilled it everywhere.

328
00:31:20,305 --> 00:31:22,065
-It's all over you.
-Come here.

329
00:31:50,345 --> 00:31:51,545
Piang.

330
00:31:54,825 --> 00:31:56,665
Can I sleep with you?

331
00:31:57,705 --> 00:31:59,385
We came all this way together.

332
00:31:59,465 --> 00:32:00,985
We can't sleep separately.

333
00:32:01,065 --> 00:32:04,985
-But your wrist…
-Don't worry about hurting me.

334
00:32:05,625 --> 00:32:09,425
Even if we sleep apart,
it still hurts when I toss and turn.

335
00:32:09,505 --> 00:32:13,105
I've endured worse when you did it.

336
00:32:13,785 --> 00:32:15,225
I even liked it.

337
00:32:15,305 --> 00:32:16,825
Piang.

338
00:32:19,505 --> 00:32:21,665
Please, Song.

339
00:32:21,745 --> 00:32:23,705
Let me sleep with you.

340
00:32:27,265 --> 00:32:28,785
Please.

341
00:32:29,385 --> 00:32:30,905
Please.

342
00:32:32,625 --> 00:32:34,145
Okay.

343
00:32:34,865 --> 00:32:36,545
Then get back into bed.

344
00:32:43,305 --> 00:32:44,345
Let's go.

345
00:33:00,425 --> 00:33:01,305
Sleep carefully.

346
00:33:02,665 --> 00:33:04,505
I don't want to hurt your wrist.

347
00:33:06,665 --> 00:33:08,585
What does "sleep carefully" mean?

348
00:33:35,185 --> 00:33:37,065
Sweet dreams, Song.

349
00:34:11,945 --> 00:34:13,505
Wake up.

350
00:34:18,025 --> 00:34:19,264
I've been awake for a while.

351
00:34:20,505 --> 00:34:21,985
Then why haven't you gotten up?

352
00:34:25,585 --> 00:34:28,065
I want to stay like this a little longer.

353
00:34:32,425 --> 00:34:34,585
But my arm's gone numb.

354
00:34:46,185 --> 00:34:47,585
Then I'll get up.

355
00:34:47,665 --> 00:34:50,985
But promise me first
you'll sleep with me again tonight.

356
00:34:53,105 --> 00:34:54,985
And every night after that.

357
00:34:55,065 --> 00:34:57,425
How many nights are you planning to stay?

358
00:35:00,905 --> 00:35:02,585
Until you finally…

359
00:35:09,305 --> 00:35:11,385
finally…

360
00:35:12,465 --> 00:35:14,225
say yes to me one more time.

361
00:35:20,425 --> 00:35:22,865
You may not be worried about your wrist,

362
00:35:23,545 --> 00:35:24,865
but with that cast,

363
00:35:25,465 --> 00:35:27,265
you can't really use that hand.

364
00:35:28,585 --> 00:35:30,465
But this hand still works.

365
00:35:33,745 --> 00:35:35,265
And…

366
00:35:43,865 --> 00:35:45,185
Are you running away because you're shy?

367
00:35:45,265 --> 00:35:46,225
No.

368
00:35:46,305 --> 00:35:47,345
I'm going to take a shower.

369
00:35:48,185 --> 00:35:50,265
If you want to shower together, hurry up.

370
00:35:50,345 --> 00:35:52,305
So we can head out.

371
00:35:53,745 --> 00:35:54,945
Okay.

372
00:37:31,025 --> 00:37:32,265
It's so beautiful.

373
00:37:35,385 --> 00:37:36,385
It is.

374
00:37:37,305 --> 00:37:39,225
It's so beautiful, it feels like a dream.

375
00:37:41,065 --> 00:37:43,545
Thank you for bringing me here.

376
00:37:44,065 --> 00:37:46,305
I'm so happy.

377
00:37:47,665 --> 00:37:50,505
I hope we can come here together again.

378
00:38:13,905 --> 00:38:14,945
Song.

379
00:38:16,785 --> 00:38:18,465
Would you like to dance with me?

380
00:38:19,465 --> 00:38:21,305
I can't dance.

381
00:38:21,385 --> 00:38:23,665
I only know how to dance in clubs.

382
00:38:23,745 --> 00:38:25,785
Then I'll lead.

383
00:38:25,865 --> 00:38:27,785
I'm actually really good at it.

384
00:38:28,665 --> 00:38:31,185
-Really?
-Mm. Really.

385
00:38:32,105 --> 00:38:34,185
My grandma loves dancing.

386
00:38:34,265 --> 00:38:37,185
So she had Mudmee and me
take dance lessons since we were kids.

387
00:38:37,865 --> 00:38:40,745
Our teacher even became
close friends with Grandma.

388
00:38:41,945 --> 00:38:45,305
Now she often invites
our teacher over for dinner.

389
00:38:45,385 --> 00:38:47,545
Then they dance together afterward.

390
00:38:53,225 --> 00:38:54,105
Come on.

391
00:38:56,265 --> 00:38:57,665
Can we dance with just one hand?

392
00:38:59,625 --> 00:39:00,865
We can.

393
00:39:00,945 --> 00:39:02,625
There are many kinds of dancing.

394
00:39:03,625 --> 00:39:04,625
Let's go.

395
00:39:58,865 --> 00:39:59,945
Song.

396
00:40:03,905 --> 00:40:08,665
I don't know…
how you'll feel if I say this now.

397
00:40:11,265 --> 00:40:12,945
But please let me say it.

398
00:40:23,625 --> 00:40:25,265
I love you.

399
00:42:10,825 --> 00:42:12,745
Let me do it.

400
00:42:58,465 --> 00:42:59,865
I told you,

401
00:43:00,745 --> 00:43:02,145
not to use this hand.

402
00:43:18,465 --> 00:43:20,225
Song, what are you doing?

403
00:43:21,505 --> 00:43:22,585
You'll see.

404
00:43:35,385 --> 00:43:37,145
Keep your wrist like this.

405
00:43:38,105 --> 00:43:39,585
Don't lower it.

406
00:43:40,945 --> 00:43:42,265
Or I'll stop.

407
00:43:49,145 --> 00:43:50,545
And…

408
00:43:55,225 --> 00:43:56,585
be patient.

409
00:43:57,665 --> 00:43:59,505
Until I'm satisfied.

410
00:44:56,425 --> 00:44:59,385
The Mega Excellent Awards are next week.

411
00:45:00,025 --> 00:45:01,945
The ceremony will be on the rooftop.

412
00:45:08,945 --> 00:45:10,785
Song, don't be afraid.

413
00:45:12,065 --> 00:45:13,985
I'll be there with you.

414
00:45:40,665 --> 00:45:43,025
-Today I'm wearing a polka-dot look.
-You went all out?

415
00:45:43,105 --> 00:45:45,705
-And yours are black and white.
-Yeah.

416
00:46:05,265 --> 00:46:06,105
Let's go.

417
00:46:07,025 --> 00:46:08,865
Let's head up, Song.

418
00:46:17,985 --> 00:46:20,105
There are many VIP guests here.

419
00:46:22,985 --> 00:46:26,265
Behave like the company's heir.

420
00:46:28,105 --> 00:46:29,345
Go with Grandma first.

421
00:46:29,425 --> 00:46:30,665
I'll catch up.

422
00:46:32,345 --> 00:46:34,425
Go on. Don't worry about me.

423
00:46:56,545 --> 00:46:58,825
-Yes.
-But you made it happen.

424
00:46:58,905 --> 00:47:01,425
-Madam President.
-Yes.

425
00:47:01,505 --> 00:47:02,545
Hello.

426
00:47:02,625 --> 00:47:05,505
-Hello, Piang. Hello, Boss.
-Hello.

427
00:47:07,425 --> 00:47:09,025
Ploy, call Song.

428
00:47:09,105 --> 00:47:10,345
Why isn't she here yet?

429
00:47:10,425 --> 00:47:11,945
The award ceremony is about to start.

430
00:47:12,025 --> 00:47:13,585
She has to go accept the award.

431
00:47:17,425 --> 00:47:19,345
Hurry.

432
00:47:19,425 --> 00:47:20,945
-Hurry.
-Hello.

433
00:47:21,025 --> 00:47:23,865
Welcome, everyone,

434
00:47:23,945 --> 00:47:28,545
to the 2026 Mega Excellent Awards.

435
00:47:28,625 --> 00:47:31,745
This event is hosted by

436
00:47:31,825 --> 00:47:37,585
126 Food to honor outstanding employees

437
00:47:37,665 --> 00:47:39,825
and boost everyone's morale.

438
00:47:40,345 --> 00:47:41,505
Did she answer?

439
00:47:42,745 --> 00:47:44,345
-She's not picking up.
-Then text her.

440
00:47:44,425 --> 00:47:45,785
Where is she?

441
00:47:46,305 --> 00:47:49,625
Song is never late. She's so responsible.

442
00:47:50,145 --> 00:47:51,545
She's not replying either.

443
00:47:54,625 --> 00:47:56,465
Without further delay,

444
00:47:56,545 --> 00:48:00,065
please welcome our president,

445
00:48:00,145 --> 00:48:02,105
Duangphamorn Chatpimuk,

446
00:48:02,185 --> 00:48:05,745
to present this year's
Outstanding Researcher Award.

447
00:48:05,825 --> 00:48:08,825
Please give our president
a warm round of applause.

448
00:48:15,825 --> 00:48:18,025
-She's not replying.
-Put your phone away.

449
00:48:21,265 --> 00:48:24,905
This year's Outstanding Researcher Award

450
00:48:24,985 --> 00:48:27,865
-goes to…
-Ploy.

451
00:48:28,385 --> 00:48:31,065
She's not answering her phone.
What do we do?

452
00:48:32,145 --> 00:48:33,145
Miss Sadanun.

453
00:48:33,225 --> 00:48:37,105
From Research Team B.

454
00:48:50,345 --> 00:48:52,105
Is Miss Sadanun here?

455
00:49:03,025 --> 00:49:04,265
<i>Song.</i>

456
00:49:04,865 --> 00:49:07,145
-I'm sorry.
-Neung.

457
00:49:09,305 --> 00:49:11,745
<i>I really can't stay. I'm sorry.</i>

458
00:49:11,825 --> 00:49:13,505
<i>Don't forget your promise.</i>

459
00:49:18,305 --> 00:49:21,185
Please come up and accept
your award, Song Sadanun.

460
00:49:21,265 --> 00:49:23,145
Hey, someone fainted!

461
00:49:23,225 --> 00:49:24,425
Hey!

462
00:49:27,745 --> 00:49:29,145
Song!

463
00:49:29,905 --> 00:49:30,905
Song, what's wrong?

464
00:49:33,465 --> 00:49:35,985
You're okay. I'm here now.

465
00:49:36,065 --> 00:49:36,945
Song.

466
00:49:39,665 --> 00:49:40,705
Song!

467
00:49:41,745 --> 00:49:42,905
-Song!
-Song!

468
00:49:43,425 --> 00:49:44,465
What's wrong?

469
00:49:44,545 --> 00:49:47,145
Why did you suddenly collapse?

470
00:49:47,945 --> 00:49:50,425
Piang, get Song out of here first.

471
00:49:50,505 --> 00:49:52,105
I'll take care of the award.

472
00:49:52,185 --> 00:49:54,065
Okay. I'm counting on you.

473
00:49:54,825 --> 00:49:56,505
-Song.
-Song, are you okay?

474
00:50:00,425 --> 00:50:02,745
It's okay now, Song.

475
00:50:18,465 --> 00:50:19,665
Thank you.

476
00:50:20,705 --> 00:50:22,665
You don't have to thank me.

477
00:50:24,585 --> 00:50:26,145
I told you,

478
00:50:26,745 --> 00:50:30,785
I'd protect you,
just like you protected me.

479
00:50:32,825 --> 00:50:35,225
By now, your grandma must…

480
00:50:35,745 --> 00:50:37,105
It's okay.

481
00:50:37,185 --> 00:50:39,545
I'm more worried about you.

482
00:50:56,865 --> 00:50:59,105
Do you remember

483
00:51:00,505 --> 00:51:03,505
when I told you I lost a family member?

484
00:51:08,585 --> 00:51:09,905
I do.

485
00:51:11,385 --> 00:51:14,105
She was my twin sister.

486
00:51:18,065 --> 00:51:19,185
Her name was Neung.

487
00:51:28,265 --> 00:51:31,545
She chose to end her life on a rooftop…

488
00:51:33,185 --> 00:51:34,985
eight years ago.

489
00:51:39,545 --> 00:51:41,385
And I was there too.

490
00:51:47,185 --> 00:51:49,385
She left this world in so much pain.

491
00:51:50,665 --> 00:51:53,465
Not only could I do nothing to help her,

492
00:51:54,825 --> 00:51:57,985
I was part of that pain too.

493
00:51:58,945 --> 00:52:01,825
Did Neung tell you that?

494
00:52:02,625 --> 00:52:03,705
No.

495
00:52:05,465 --> 00:52:07,505
But it's true.

496
00:52:11,625 --> 00:52:15,545
I keep having the same dream
almost every night.

497
00:52:17,145 --> 00:52:20,785
And whenever I go somewhere like that,

498
00:52:23,705 --> 00:52:25,825
it all comes back.

499
00:52:27,145 --> 00:52:29,825
It's as if she's always reminding me

500
00:52:30,505 --> 00:52:33,345
that she left this world in pain.

501
00:52:35,225 --> 00:52:38,465
So I don't deserve to be happy either.

502
00:52:40,985 --> 00:52:42,465
Song.

503
00:52:45,585 --> 00:52:48,385
I don't know what really happened,

504
00:52:50,905 --> 00:52:55,425
but if I were Neung,
I would never think that way.

505
00:52:56,905 --> 00:52:58,465
I would…

506
00:52:59,465 --> 00:53:01,385
forgive my little sister

507
00:53:03,505 --> 00:53:07,025
and wish her happiness every single day.

508
00:53:08,985 --> 00:53:12,945
Because I know
I would never get that chance again.

509
00:53:16,465 --> 00:53:18,105
Do you really think so?

510
00:53:19,905 --> 00:53:21,025
I do.

511
00:53:23,625 --> 00:53:26,185
Even though I never knew Neung,

512
00:53:27,465 --> 00:53:30,425
I believe she felt the same way.

513
00:53:32,385 --> 00:53:35,425
The reason you still see Neung

514
00:53:35,505 --> 00:53:39,265
is because your subconscious
still blames you.

515
00:53:45,225 --> 00:53:47,345
But it's okay now.

516
00:53:48,225 --> 00:53:50,065
Please stop blaming yourself.

517
00:54:01,225 --> 00:54:04,825
Song, go ahead and cry.

518
00:54:16,865 --> 00:54:19,625
Let my shoulder catch your tears.

519
00:55:03,705 --> 00:55:04,865
Yes.

520
00:55:07,105 --> 00:55:07,985
Who is that?

521
00:55:23,385 --> 00:55:24,385
Dad.

522
00:55:24,465 --> 00:55:25,305
Wait.

523
00:55:29,905 --> 00:55:31,185
You're not even going to welcome me?

524
00:55:31,265 --> 00:55:32,785
It took me forever to find you.

525
00:55:34,145 --> 00:55:35,665
Looks like you're doing just fine.

526
00:55:47,545 --> 00:55:49,025
<i>Song is feeling better now.</i>

527
00:56:03,145 --> 00:56:04,185
Dad, just go.

528
00:56:04,265 --> 00:56:05,705
-I don't have money for you.
-I don't buy that.

529
00:56:05,785 --> 00:56:07,185
It's only twenty or thirty thousand.

530
00:56:07,265 --> 00:56:08,145
How could you not have it?

531
00:56:08,225 --> 00:56:09,345
I'm your father.

532
00:56:09,425 --> 00:56:10,865
You're not my father.

533
00:56:10,945 --> 00:56:12,825
Ever since you and Mom abandoned me.

534
00:56:22,585 --> 00:56:23,785
Ple!

535
00:56:30,105 --> 00:56:31,745
Don't you dare lay a hand on me.

536
00:56:33,145 --> 00:56:35,105
I'm not Mom. I won't let you.

537
00:56:35,185 --> 00:56:36,465
What the hell are you gonna do?

538
00:56:36,545 --> 00:56:38,145
I'll fight back.

539
00:56:38,225 --> 00:56:39,985
-You'll fight me?
-Yes.

540
00:56:40,065 --> 00:56:42,625
Let's see how tough you really are.

541
00:56:42,705 --> 00:56:43,865
You ungrateful bitch.

542
00:56:48,585 --> 00:56:49,945
Why?

543
00:56:50,545 --> 00:56:52,865
Ple. Don't!

544
00:56:54,265 --> 00:56:56,505
-Who the hell are you?
-And who are you?

545
00:56:56,585 --> 00:56:58,425
-What do you want?
-I'm her father.

546
00:56:58,505 --> 00:57:00,585
I want money. Do you have any?

547
00:57:08,505 --> 00:57:10,465
Ploy. Don't.

548
00:57:14,065 --> 00:57:16,345
This is all I have. Take it.

549
00:57:17,385 --> 00:57:20,625
If you need anything else,
come to me instead.

550
00:57:20,705 --> 00:57:22,465
And leave her alone.

551
00:57:24,345 --> 00:57:25,625
Is she your girlfriend?

552
00:57:27,625 --> 00:57:28,545
You're damn lucky.

553
00:57:43,105 --> 00:57:44,065
Ple.

554
00:57:45,185 --> 00:57:47,025
Are you okay?

555
00:57:52,705 --> 00:57:54,225
It's okay. It's okay.

556
00:57:56,225 --> 00:57:57,425
I'm here.

557
00:58:17,705 --> 00:58:18,985
Why are you crying?

558
00:58:21,385 --> 00:58:24,625
It's just a scratch. I'm okay.

559
00:58:29,585 --> 00:58:30,545
Ploy.

560
00:58:35,625 --> 00:58:36,905
Let's break up.

561
00:58:45,905 --> 00:58:46,785
What?

562
00:58:48,425 --> 00:58:49,985
I can't take it.

563
00:58:51,665 --> 00:58:53,945
I can't watch you get hurt
because of me again.

564
00:58:55,985 --> 00:58:58,065
I know my father.

565
00:59:00,065 --> 00:59:01,825
He'll do it again.

566
00:59:03,745 --> 00:59:06,985
It's just a scratch. I'm okay.

567
00:59:07,985 --> 00:59:08,825
It's nothing.

568
00:59:08,905 --> 00:59:10,545
But it's not to me.

569
00:59:16,545 --> 00:59:17,545
Ple.

570
00:59:19,265 --> 00:59:23,545
We both helped Song and Piang

571
00:59:24,265 --> 00:59:25,825
find their way to each other.

572
00:59:25,905 --> 00:59:28,545
So why, when it comes to us,

573
00:59:29,785 --> 00:59:31,105
are you the one letting go?

574
00:59:35,905 --> 00:59:37,545
Let's get through this together.

575
00:59:40,385 --> 00:59:41,305
Please.

576
00:59:59,665 --> 01:00:00,745
Okay.

577
01:00:04,225 --> 01:00:05,945
If you really want to break up,

578
01:00:06,745 --> 01:00:07,785
then okay.

579
01:00:14,145 --> 01:00:16,105
But let me say one thing.

580
01:00:18,425 --> 01:00:20,985
The pain you're facing now…

581
01:00:22,465 --> 01:00:24,305
you've overcome it before.

582
01:00:27,305 --> 01:00:29,425
Don't let it hurt you again.

583
01:00:33,425 --> 01:00:34,745
Take care.

584
01:01:43,905 --> 01:01:45,505
Song, get some sleep.

585
01:01:45,585 --> 01:01:48,025
I'll stay right here with you.

586
01:01:49,305 --> 01:01:51,625
I was supposed to be
the one taking care of you.

587
01:01:52,185 --> 01:01:54,305
Now you're the one taking care of me.

588
01:01:56,425 --> 01:01:59,145
That's okay. I want to.

589
01:01:59,785 --> 01:02:01,945
I like doing it too.

590
01:02:03,065 --> 01:02:04,945
If my hand weren't injured,

591
01:02:05,025 --> 01:02:07,185
you'd be eating my
chocolate muffins already.

592
01:02:07,265 --> 01:02:09,105
Haven't you learned?

593
01:02:09,665 --> 01:02:11,705
I threw away the whole box last time.

594
01:02:12,465 --> 01:02:14,225
Then I need to keep baking.

595
01:02:14,305 --> 01:02:15,985
Until you finally eat one.

596
01:02:22,145 --> 01:02:25,345
So when will your hand heal?

597
01:02:28,825 --> 01:02:30,465
I don't know.

598
01:02:32,665 --> 01:02:34,545
Then wait for me.

599
01:02:35,265 --> 01:02:36,585
Don't go anywhere yet.

600
01:02:39,905 --> 01:02:41,425
Get some sleep.

601
01:03:46,225 --> 01:03:47,305
Oh.

602
01:03:48,385 --> 01:03:50,225
I have to go to the office today.

603
01:03:50,305 --> 01:03:51,705
I have something to take care of.

604
01:03:54,745 --> 01:03:57,625
Then can I come with you?

605
01:03:57,705 --> 01:04:00,825
I want to stay by your side all day today.

606
01:04:02,305 --> 01:04:03,705
Why today?

607
01:04:06,145 --> 01:04:07,345
It's nothing.

608
01:04:07,425 --> 01:04:09,985
I just… want to be with you every day.

609
01:04:10,785 --> 01:04:12,065
Wait here for me.

610
01:04:12,145 --> 01:04:13,905
I'll just grab my bag.

611
01:04:25,625 --> 01:04:26,665
Let's go.

612
01:05:07,265 --> 01:05:08,345
Boss.

613
01:05:13,345 --> 01:05:15,385
I'd like to resign.

614
01:05:21,425 --> 01:05:22,665
It's been two weeks already?

615
01:05:23,265 --> 01:05:25,305
So you knew about it?

616
01:05:26,585 --> 01:05:27,585
Mm.

617
01:05:28,865 --> 01:05:29,985
But…

618
01:05:30,625 --> 01:05:32,905
I'd like you to think it over again.

619
01:05:33,785 --> 01:05:35,465
Follow your heart.

620
01:05:35,545 --> 01:05:37,705
Forget about that promise.

621
01:05:38,465 --> 01:05:39,465
Let me…

622
01:05:40,505 --> 01:05:42,305
be the only one who suffers.

623
01:05:43,265 --> 01:05:45,345
I want to see my little sister happy.

624
01:05:49,225 --> 01:05:51,465
I've made up my mind, Boss.

625
01:05:55,185 --> 01:05:56,105
All right.

626
01:05:58,065 --> 01:06:02,425
If you've made up your mind,
I'll respect your decision.

627
01:06:03,225 --> 01:06:04,945
Thank you, Boss.

628
01:06:07,145 --> 01:06:08,505
I'll get going now.

629
01:06:23,585 --> 01:06:25,345
Why are you standing here?

630
01:06:28,985 --> 01:06:32,945
I told you,
I'd stay as close to you as I could.

631
01:06:39,745 --> 01:06:40,825
Song.

632
01:06:42,665 --> 01:06:46,025
Can I ask you something honestly?

633
01:06:51,665 --> 01:06:53,745
All this time…

634
01:06:54,865 --> 01:06:56,825
we've spent together…

635
01:07:10,465 --> 01:07:12,785
Have you ever felt anything for me?

636
01:07:17,665 --> 01:07:18,665
Felt…

637
01:07:19,585 --> 01:07:20,705
what?

638
01:07:22,705 --> 01:07:24,225
Do you love me?

639
01:07:28,865 --> 01:07:30,585
Why are you asking me that?

640
01:07:37,065 --> 01:07:38,825
I just want to know.

641
01:07:58,985 --> 01:08:00,505
Please don't stay silent.

642
01:08:07,025 --> 01:08:08,025
This…

643
01:08:13,985 --> 01:08:15,545
is my answer.

644
01:08:27,265 --> 01:08:28,544
Okay.

645
01:08:32,544 --> 01:08:34,185
I understand.

646
01:08:41,105 --> 01:08:42,705
I give up.

647
01:09:50,985 --> 01:09:54,225
Song didn't choose me, Grandma.

648
01:09:54,305 --> 01:09:55,985
<i>I give up.</i>

649
01:09:57,625 --> 01:09:58,945
<i>Go to sleep, Piang.</i>

650
01:09:59,025 --> 01:10:00,905
<i>Just think of it as a bad dream.</i>

651
01:10:00,985 --> 01:10:03,665
<i>I think you should ask yourself, Grandma,</i>

652
01:10:03,745 --> 01:10:09,465
whether what you want
or what Piang feels matters more.

653
01:10:09,545 --> 01:10:11,305
When we're around other people,

654
01:10:11,385 --> 01:10:13,585
<i>I think we should pretend</i>
<i>we're still together.</i>

655
01:10:14,345 --> 01:10:16,225
<i>I've shared your pain, Neung.</i>

656
01:10:16,825 --> 01:10:18,065
<i>You don't have to bear it alone anymore.</i>

